# Tests

When you add or change behavior in this repo, **always add or update tests** so the change is covered.

- **Go:** put tests in `*_test.go` next to the code (or in a `testdata/` layout when needed). Prefer table-driven tests for multiple cases.
- **Run:** `go test ./...` (or the narrowest package path) and fix failures before finishing.
- Do not merge or hand off work with only manual verification when automated tests are practical.

```go
// Example: add a case per format or edge case you support
tests := []struct {
	name    string
	input   string
	wantErr bool
}{
	{"iso", "2026-04-04", false},
	{"invalid", "not-a-date", true},
}
for _, tt := range tests {
	t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) { /* ... */ })
}
```
